post_text: I wanted you to know that we continue to be in contact with Goodland Regional Weather about the snow storm and are continuing to monitor the situation. As of right now, we feel like we have the students in school and they are in a good place. Calling off school right now and putting busses and students on the road ways does not sound like a good option. They are telling us that the heaviest snow is falling right now and should be letting up soon. We will have another conference call at 11:00 am and will make a decision then and the rest of the day. Stay Tuned!

post_text: Just a reminder that we are having a presentation & discussion on our Apollo Redesign project and invite all parents and community members to attend. It will be held at the HS auditorium tonight at 6:00 pm. We will review a few key concepts of our "Why", hear from all 3 buildings on what they are doing, what they are looking at, and plans. We will then seek ask you a series of questions to collect data and seek your input. We will end with some Q&A time. Our goal is for the meeting to last 1 1/2 hours.

post_text: Our 2nd Community / parent meeting to discuss our Apollo redesign project has been scheduled for Jan. 20th, 6:00 pm, at the HS auditorium. All parents and community members are encouraged and welcome to attend. We had a great group of people who showed up at our first meeting where we just laid some foundational ideas and concepts. This time we will be digging deeper and seeking input from the community so please plan to attend. You did not have to attend the first meeting to come to this one.

post_text: Dear Parents, we would like to have parent information meeting on Nov. 4th, 6:00 pm at the HS cafeteria. The purpose of the meeting will be to discuss our Redesign efforts, where we are going as a district, what we are currently doing, and overall vision. We really do want parent input into this process and would value your presence at this meeting. So mark your calendar and come join us for a conversation about the future of education in Goodland.

post_text:
Cowboy GROW
Summer Learning Opportunity

Get ready for some fun and excitement! Join us for a hands-on learning opportunity based on gardening. Do you know what it takes to grow your own vegetables? Do you know which plants like each other and which ones don‚Äôt? This project-based learning project will include literacy and math skills as you learn about gardening and nutrition. At the end of the project, you get to take your garden home with you to care for throughout the rest of the summer! You will learn what you need to do to keep your garden growing. The great news is that there is no cost involved for the family!

WHEN: June 4th through June 27th
DAYS: Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays
TIME: 8:00 a.m. - 11:00 a.m.
WHERE: North Elementary
WHO: Kindergarten through 8th Grade

Visit our website, www.usd352.org for more information and to signup.

Tuesday, May 23rd - Last Day of School

The Board of Education decided at their regular scheduled meeting last night to move the last day of school to Tuesday, May 23rd. Due to the fact that the district has not used very many of its alotted snow days this year, the district will still exceed the required number of hours for students. The BOE thought this was a great way to acknowledge our staff and students for a great year. If you have any questions please contact your building principal or superintendent Bill Biermann. Thanks.

post_text:
Yesterday, Jade Artzer, attended the Kansas E-Challenge hosted by Kansas State University. She was one of about 20 competitors (in the HS division) that was accepted and invited to attend the competition with her business, Made by Jade.

Jade presented to a small panel of judges in the preliminaries and was selected for the finals. She then presented to the entire panel of judges and was selected as the 3rd place winner. With that comes a $2,500 prize!

Next Monday, April 24th, Jade will be headed to Fort Hays State University to compete in the State Youth Entrepreneurship Challenge, sponsored by Network Kansas. She will have another opportunity to win a cash prize that will be used to help grow her business.

Congrats, Jade!

I thought this might be of interest to some of you, so just passing it on:

http://www.granthistoric.com/

The link above is info about the Grant Jr. High Apartments that are currently being remodeled and almost available to lease. The building was built in 1926 and severed as Grant Elementary School until 1969 then it was transitioned into the Jr High and served students for another 46 years. The building was placed on the National Historic Register and now an apartment community and historic landmark.

post_text:
If you would to help us get a new mascot, see below, and vote everyday!

KAKE news is hosting an online Mascot Mania competition for the chance to win a brand new mascot! The schools across Kansas are divided up in accordance to student enrollment and region. You can vote once a day every single day!

October 8th the competition will be narrowed down to the 5 highest scoring schools (1 winner in each region) and the regional winners will receive $1000 prize!

The "Final 5" competition will end Friday, November 4th on the KAKE 10pm news, with the announcement of the over all winner. The overall winner receives a brand new CUSTOM Mascot!
Vote every day, and share the link to social media so the community can vote as well!

Here is the link to go to in order to vote: http://kake.secondstreetapp.com/l/Mascot-Mania-2016

post_text:
Come and get them - Old Lockers

The school district has taken the newer lockers out of GJH and moved them over to the MAX to replace the original lockers. We are just going to set these outside the MAX to give them back to the community for supporting us. We would ask that you just take one set of lockers if you want them today to give everyone a chance if they want one. Whatever is left tomorrow, you can come and get as many as you want until they are gone. Please be respectful to one another and thanks for supporting USD 352. If you have questions give me call 890-2397 or shoot me an email bill.biermann@usd352.org

Our first game is at 11:00 today and we will just get every contest started early if we can. Please share with as many people as possible and spread he word. Our hope would be that he championship game could start as early as 5:15 instead of 7:00

post_text:
District Office has Moved.

The District Office and Central Administration has now officially moved across the street to the 2nd floor of what was Central Elementary School. 1311 Main. All contact information is the same, but if you need to visit in person with the Superintendent or any support staff, please come and see us. For the next couple of months the Board of Education meetings will still be conducted at the old office, 1312 Main, as we have not yet moved that space over. Eventually, the Board room will be in the old Central Elementary Library.
